Review control description: (13) "overcollateralisation" means any form of credit enhancement by virtue of
which underlying exposures are posted in value which is higher than the value
of the securitisation notes;

Review control description: (22) "senior tranche" means a tranche which is effectively backed or secured by
a first claim on the entire amount of the assets in the underlying securitised
pool;

Review control description: An NBFC shall not undertake the securitisation activities or assume securitisation
exposures as mentioned below:
